# SEQUENCE 05 — THE PRINCE AND THE SHADOW

/* TRACE: FU-025 | SC-107 */

INT. CHITRAPATHI'S RECEIVING ROOM — LATE AFTERNOON #35#

CHITRAPATHI receives UDAYAKUMARAN without ceremony.

The room carries the evidence of an artistic household under strain: instruments kept in repair, account cords retied, a costume chest left unopened.

CHITRAPATHI
A house like ours survives because powerful people remember its value.

UDAYAKUMARAN
You asked for me because Manimekalai has forgotten mine.

CHITRAPATHI
No. I asked you because you have forgotten hers.

A silence.

The prince is not insulted by the words. He is unsettled because they are spoken calmly.

/* TRACE: FU-026 | SC-109 */

EXT. PUHAR — FLOWER GARDEN — EVENING #36#

Manimekalai and Sudhamathi gather flowers for lamps.

The garden is not a romantic space. It is a public space temporarily quiet.

UDAYAKUMARAN watches from a distance.

He does not see a person at peace. He sees distance between himself and what he wants.

SUDHAMATHI notices him first.

SUDHAMATHI
We leave now.

MANIMEKALAI
I have done nothing wrong.

SUDHAMATHI
That is not the only question a dangerous person asks.

/* TRACE: FU-027 | SC-110 */

EXT. FLOWER GARDEN PATH — CONTINUOUS #37#

Udayakumaran approaches.

His voice remains gentle. The gentleness makes the refusal harder for him to accept.

UDAYAKUMARAN
I have crossed only a few steps.

MANIMEKALAI
For you, perhaps.

She steps back.

MANIMEKALAI (CONT'D)
For me, every step decides who I am allowed to become.

The prince hears rejection as loss rather than as information.

/* TRACE: FU-028 | SC-111 */

INT. PALACE CHAMBER — NIGHT #38#

The prince's attendants describe Manimekalai's movements as though reporting a military problem.

A trusted elder interrupts.

ELDER
A person refusing you is not a kingdom refusing you.

UDAYAKUMARAN
You think I do not know the difference?

ELDER
I think you know it in words.

The prince turns away.

/* TRACE: FU-029 | SC-112 */

EXT. PUHAR — SACRED SPACE — NIGHT #39#

Manimekalai seeks refuge in stillness.

She does not ask for the world to disappear. She asks how to move through it without becoming what others expect.

The city continues around her.

/* TRACE: FU-030 | SC-113 */

INT. MADHAVI'S HOUSE — NIGHT #40#

Madhavi learns that the prince continues to search.

MADHAVI
My daughter is not a second chance for my past.

Chitrapathi looks at her.

CHITRAPATHI
Then help her make a future.

/* TRACE: FU-031 | SC-114 */

EXT. PUHAR — NIGHT STREETS #41#

Rumours travel faster than facts.

One person says the prince loves.
Another says he is entitled.
Another says they do not know.

The city reveals itself through uncertainty.

/* TRACE: FU-032 | SC-115 */

EXT. SACRED SPACE / CITY EDGE — NIGHT #42#

Manimekalai is separated from pursuit.

The boundary between escape and responsibility disappears.

She does not know that the next movement will transform her life.

/* TRACE: FU-033 | SC-116 */

EXT. PUHAR — DAWN #43#

The city wakes.

A prince searches for what he believes he has lost.

A woman begins a journey toward what she has not yet found.

END SEQUENCE 05